args:
New Year's has arrived, and as people delight
in the kimonos they receive from Ieyasu,
the hospitality face-off begins with a battle
of osechi. Botan offers up hers with confidence,
but ends up losing to Sazanka's flawless food.
Happy New Year, one and all!
We've made it to another year.
I must say, that sudden competition made\nme worry about your true intentions.
My apologies if I caused you undue worry.
But it was worth it, 'cause we got one\nheckuva show!
I learned quite a bit from seeing your\nstyle up close like that.
Yeah, that's all well and good, but let's get\nback to the otoshidama gift thing. Is it\nreally just these tiny little fragments?
Ah, but you are all quite formidable.\nI fear I must yield to you.
As promised, allow me to give you these.
I feel like I've seen these fragments\nbefore, but maybe not?
Aren't these otherworld fragments?\nThe ones with the power to warp space!
Then you are familiar with them?\nMost interesting.
In our land, we call them ＂heavenly\ngleamshards,＂ or just gleamshards.
These were given to us by Amaterasu for\nlater entertainment.
I'm confident you'll enjoy it.\nHowever, before that happens,\nplease take these as a souvenir.
I look pretty sharp in these duds, yeah?
I'm a bit shy about all the brilliant colors,\nbut I suppose there's nothing wrong with\na little showiness now and again.
The quality of these garments is\nimpeccable. Are you certain you\nwish to part with them so easily?
It is what Master Ieyasu commands.
I can't believe you even thought to bring\none that would fit Notte.
We brought all manner of sizes,\nas we were uncertain what people\nmight dwell in other lands.
I'm glad to see we had something suitable.
And with this, our preparations are\ncomplete, and the hospitality face-off\ncan begin in earnest!
Hospitality Face-Off\nRound One: Osechi\nBotan VS Sazanka
So this ＂osechi＂ stuff is food, right?
I feel as though I can see what the\noutcome is going to be already.
D-don't be so sure! I taste-tested it this\ntime and everything!
Hate to say it, Botan, but yer pretty much\noutclassed here.
I fear I must agree. Not only is the other\nseasoning superior, but the presentation\nis beyond reproach.
H-hey now! Botan's osechi wasn't bad!
In that case, why were you forcing it down\nwith literal goblets of water?
You're so good at cooking, Sazanka.\nThat was stupid delicious.
You honor me far too much. I am merely\ncarrying out my duties.
Urgh... I guess I can't beat Sazanka's\ncooking after all.
But we're not done yet; I've still got a\nchance to turn this baby around!
